<chapter id="policy_manager">
  <title>Policy Manager</title>

  <para>
    The Policy Manager is a powerful and advanced feature of the &eg;.  It lets Administrators alter the behavior of their &eg; based on the network interface and/or endpoints of connections.  For more information on the network interfaces available to your &eg;, please refer to <xref linkend="fixme_interfaces"/>.
  </para>
  <para>
    The Policy Manager is launched from the main Administrative Interface by selecting <guilabel>Show Policy Manager</guilabel> as seen in <xref linkend="policy_manager_launch_policy_mngr"/>.
  </para>
  <figure id="policy_manager_launch_policy_mngr">
    <title>Launching the Policy Manager</title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="figure/policymngr/launch_policy_mngr.png" />
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>    
  <para>
    The Policy Manager works by creating rules.  A rule binds traffic matching certain criteria to a Virtual Rack.  For an overview of Policies and Virtual Racks, please refer to <xref linkend="policy_manager_overview"/>.  For modification of the default policies, please refer to <xref linkend="policy_manager_def_policies"/>.  To create your own Virtual Racks and assign them to Policies, please refer to <xref linkend="policy_manager_available_racks"/> and <xref linkend="policy_manager_custom_policies"/>.
  </para>


